      "name": "Hemolysis index benchmark comparison — 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 flow-speed combinations. Mean absolute error 38%; model systematically under-predicts peak shear-stress regions. Validation activity conducted on FDA generic pump geometry; gap to VAD COU geometry remains unquantified."
