      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy verification for all governing equations including scalar transport used in hemolysis model, demonstrated on manufactured solutions.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy verified for Navier-Stokes equations on canonical geometries. Scalar transport equation underpinning the power-law hemolysis model has not been subjected to manufactured-solution verification. Gap identified as critical at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI reported for hemolysis QoI on at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI < 5% for NIH.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh refinement study performed; GCI for velocity field is 4.2%. GCI for NIH scalar is 21%, exceeding the 5% threshold. Near-wall mesh resolution in blade passages remains insufficient for hemolysis prediction at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
